text:
Keep scrolling for Sarah Jessica Parker's 64 most memorable fashion moments throughout the years.

While Carrie and SJP share some designer faves (looking at you, Vivienne Westwood), the actress has her own off-screen go-tos—like Oscar de la Renta and Chanel. From the gold-bra-and-sequined-jacket-combo she stepped out in for one of her first red carpets to the iconic Dior newspaper dress she wore playing Carrie Bradshaw, SJP has spent the better part of the last 30 years showing she's got the fashion game down.

There is absolutely no denying the sartorial power of Sarah Jessica Parker , whether she's donning garments as herself or as Carrie Bradshaw . As the latter, SJP has worn clothes, shoes, and bags from Dior, Fendi, Manolo Blahnik, and Vivienne Westwood (who designed the famous Sex and the City wedding dress). But even when she's not on the set, Parker's put together some of the most memorable looks around. Her style is fashion-forward, but it also has a playful and whimsical energy that's innate to the actress.

01 of 64 Make a Statement Sarah Jessica Parker in an embellished jacket, red velvet pants, and a gold bra in 1991. Barry King/WireImage In true SJP fashion, the star showed off an embellished jacket, red velvet pants, and her signature abs at the film premiere of For The Boys. Every part of the ensemble worked together for perfect synergy.

02 of 64 Tutu Cute Sarah Jessica Parker as Carrie Bradshaw while wearing a light pink top and a white tutu in 1998. Fame Pictures, Inc Much like the famed Dior newspaper dress, the white tutu that Carrie Bradshaw dons in the opening sequence of Sex and the City and its first film is a significant part of pop culture history. "I remember I bought that tutu for $5," says series costume designer Rebecca Weinberg. "Our seamstress had to duplicate it because we knew in the sequence it was going to get wet."

03 of 64 Shoulderless Suit Sarah Jessica Parker wearing a gray Vivienne Westwood suit and matching clutch in 2000. Ke.Mazur/WireImage For the SAG Awards, the Failure to Launch star wore a gray Vivienne Westwood suit and matching clutch. Of course, she had to add her own twist and make the chic suit off the shoulder.

04 of 64 The Newspaper Dress Sarah Jessica Parker in the Dior newspaper dress in 2000. Craig Blankenhorn/New Line Cinema Best known for making two appearances on Sex and the City, the famed Dior newspaper dress is almost as iconic as Carrie Bradshaw herself. In fact, in May 2025, Jenna Ortega wore the very same dress to the Hurry Up Tomorrow world premiere in NYC.

05 of 64 Fairy Ballerina Sarah Jessica Parker in a pink, ballerina-inspired feathered dress by Oscar de la Renta in 2000. Ron Galella, Ltd./WireImage Sarah Jessica Parker chose a pink, ballerina-inspired feathered dress by Oscar de la Renta for the Emmy Awards, which was completed with a floral armband.

06 of 64 She Means Business Sarah Jessica Parker in an off-white blazer, button-down, and red pumps in 2001. KMazur/WireImage The star nailed the menswear trend, opting for an off-white blazer, button-down, and red pumps. To be sure, the blazer dress Parker is sporting here is still very much making the fashion rounds—albeit in a slightly more oversized style.

07 of 64 Princess in Pink Sarah Jessica Parker in a layered, organza soft pink dress by Chanel Couture in 2003. Chris Delmas/VISUALPressAgency.com For the 55th Annual Emmy Awards, Sarah Jessica Parker chose this layered, organza soft pink dress by Chanel Couture, which dazzled on the red carpet. As did her giant diamond ring, clutch, and dainty bracelet.

08 of 64 Gothic Glam SJP in a black corset and matching trousers by Jorgen Simonsen in 2003. WireImage For her first red carpet debut as a new mom, the actress flaunted her figure in a corset and matching trousers from Jorgen Simonsen. The ensemble turned many a head (and you can tell by the people staring in the background).

09 of 64 She Wins the Lace Sarah Jessica Parker in a pink and white Oscar de la Renta dress in 2004. Stephen Lovekin/FilmMagic Pretty in pink. The always glamorous star donned a strapless Oscar de la Renta dress for the FiFi Awards. Her blue eye makeup and oversized beaded necklace add a playful energy and colorful contrast.

10 of 64 The Wedding Dress Sarah Jessica Parker in the Vivienne Westwood wedding gown from "Sex and the City" in 2008. Pacific Coast News For the jaw-dropping wedding scene in the first installment of the Sex and the City movie, the film's costume designers turned to Vivienne Westwood for a larger-than-life gown. And who could forget that peacock headpiece?

11 of 64 Natural Sparkle Sarah Jessica Parker in a strapless silver Nina Ricci gown in 2008. Jim Spellman/WireImage Sarah Jessica Parker dazzled in a strapless silver Nina Ricci gown at the Sex And The City premiere at Radio City Music Hall in New York City. The metallic tones are a beautiful complement to her fair skin tone.

12 of 64 Old Hollywood Glam Sarah Jessica Parker in a strapless Dior Haute Couture silver gown with gold accents in 2009. Kevin Mazur/WireImage At the Academy Awards, SJP looked ethereal in a Dior Haute Couture silver gown featuring gold accents, which she accessorized with Fred Leighton jewels and long, brown, structured waves. It's giving Old Hollywood glamour.

13 of 64 In Memoriam Sarah Jessica Parker in a black and white Alexander McQueen coat and dress in 2010. Fred Duval To pay tribute to her late friend Alexander McQueen at his London memorial service, Parker donned one of his creations: a black-and-white coat dress design.

14 of 64 Ode to a Friend Sarah Jessica Parker wearing a purple and pink Alexander McQueen gown with a dark handbag in 2010. Marion Curtis/Startraksphoto The actress honored Alexander McQueen in a print gown from the late designer. To complete her look, she accessorized with Stephen Russell earrings and bracelets, plus a stingray diamond cuff and jade ring from VBH.

15 of 64 Neutral Glam Sarah Jessica Parker in a one-shoulder metallic Halston dress in 2010. Toni Passig/Getty Images Parker wore Fred Leighton vintage jewelry and a metallic asymmetric Halston dress for her first of four outfits at the Bambi Awards in Germany. To add a bit of contrast to her neutral 'fit, the Girls Just Want to Have Fun opted for a black shimmery clutch.

16 of 64 Just Fascinating Sarah Jessica Parker in a high-low Alexander McQueen gown and Philip Treacy fascinator in 2010. Rex/Rex USA For the Sex and the City 2 premiere in London, the actress wore a high-low Alexander McQueen gown with an elaborate Philip Treacy fascinator. And fascinate it did.

17 of 64 A Bubbly Personality SJP in a Proenza Schouler bubble dress topped with a pink blazer in 2010. Fame Pictures Parker strolled to a Central Park interview in a Proenza Schouler bubble dress topped with a pink blazer and accented with Nicholas Kirkwood sandals. To accent the white on her dress, she opted for a white handbag.

18 of 64 2010s in a Nutshell Sarah Jessica Parker in a white Stella McCartney blazer and pink lace dress in 2010. Henry Lamb/Photowire/BEImages At Bravo's Upfront Party in New York City, SJP wore a Stella McCartney blazer and lace dress, accessorized with black pumps, a metallic mesh bag, and layered necklaces. Anyone old enough to remember outfits in the 2010s will tell you blazer, dresses, and pumps were the winning formula.

19 of 64 Garden Variety Sarah Jessica Parker in a voluminous Vivienne Westwood gown with floral designs and a belt in 2010. AP For the Japan premiere of Sex and the City 2, Parker donned a statement-making Vivienne Westwood gown, cinching her look with a Raven Kauffman "Harlow" belt. It's like if the designer made a sartorial bouquet for the Honeymoon in Vegas co-star.

20 of 64 Legs for Days Sarah Jessica Parker in a black one-shoulder dress, polka dot tights, and a large necklace in 2010. Gregorio T. Binuya/Everett Collection Dressed in an LBD, polka-dot pantyhose, and a statement necklace, Sarah Jessica Parker walked the red carpet for the Empire State Pride Agenda Fall Dinner. Her legs look like they go on for miles, even though the petite actress is only 5'3".

21 of 64 Bold Structure Sarah Jessica Parker wearing a black sculpted tulle Marchesa minidress and black heels in 2010. Steve Marcus/Landov The actress wore a black sculpted tulle Marchesa minidress and black platform pumps at the ShoWest closing ceremony in Las Vegas. It's such a unique and interesting ensemble.

22 of 64 Butter Yellow Sarah Jessica Parker in a satin yellow dress at the Oscars in 2010. Tsuni/Gamma-USA Parker rocked a gorgeous satin yellow Chanel Couture gown at the Oscars, which had a column shape and jeweled neckline. If you're thinking this is reminiscent of the butter yellow dress from How to Lose a Guy in 10 Days, you're not the only one.

23 of 64 Featherweight Champion Sarah Jessica Parker in a in a white iridescent top, plumed Louis Vuitton skirt, and pumps in 2011. Anthony Behar/Sipa Press The actress feted UNICEF at the annual Snowflake Ball in a plumed Louis Vuitton confection that she paired with the label's calf leather pumps, Fred Leighton earrings, and stacked pavé bangles.

24 of 64 Something New Sarah Jessica Parker wearing a long-sleeved Elie Saab floral gown in 2011. Tony Barson/WireImage The Footloose co-star stepped on a red carpet in a straight-from-the-runway floral design from Elie Saab. While the dress's material is one of SJP's more pared-down looks, the accessories are what make the outfit stand out.

25 of 64 Colorblocking Sarah Jessica Parker in a sheer red Prabal Gurung cape blouse and hot pink trousers in 2011. Roger Wong/INFphoto.com Parker sat down with David Letterman in a vermilion Prabal Gurung cape blouse and hot pink trousers. Because both garments are one solid color, albeit different colors, this is a lesson in how to colorblock like a pro.

26 of 64 Make a Beeline Sarah Jessica Parker in in a rose print Prabal Gurung dress with black pumps in 2011. Ian West/PA Wire/Abaca USA At a press event at London's Soho Hotel, SJP wore a rose print Prabal Gurung design and glitter platforms. In addition to the floral accents, he yellow and black on her dress make this look bee-utiful.

27 of 64 In the Details Sarah Jessica Parker in a muted orange Antonio Berardi sweater and indigo skirt in 2011. API/Fame Pictures While in Germany to promote her film I Don't Know How She Does It, the actress wore Antonio Berardi on the red carpet. Though these pieces are more on the casual side, the details—like the black cuffs and slits on her pants—are what the 'fit is really about.

28 of 64 Keep It Casual Sarah Jessica Parker in a gray L'Agence overcoat with a black tee and torn denim jeans in 2011. Fame Pictures In London, Parker layered a knee-length L'Agence coat with a black tee and torn denim. A python L'Wren Scott tote and nude Jean-Michel Cazabat heels completed the outfit for a laid-back vibe that still feels elevated.

29 of 64 Tweed About It Sarah Jessica Parker in a tweed Chanel dress and sculptured black hat by Philip Treacy in 2011. Rex USA While in Melbourne, Australia to promote a film, the actress wore a tweed Chanel dress and sculptured black hat by Philip Treacy, which took over 200 hours to make.

30 of 64 Hero in a Cape Sarah Jessica Parker in a scarlet Giambattista Valli gown complete with a cape in 2011. Kristina Nikishina/Epsilon/Getty Images Parker attended a Moscow I Don't Know How She Does It press event in a scarlet Giambattista Valli gown complete with a cape and pavé hoops. In addition to layers, the pleats give this ensemble even more dimension.

31 of 64 Angelic Sarah Jessica Parker in an Erdem sky-blue pastel lace dress with mesh at the midriff in 2012. Nigel Waldron/Getty Images At the Nobel Peace Prize Concert, Parker took the stage in this Erdem sky-blue pastel lace design. The small section of mesh in the midriff makes it seem like this is a two-piece, which is that classic SJP attention to detail that fans are used to.

32 of 64 Showing Some Skin Sarah Jessica Parker in a sheer white lace top, fitted tea-length skirt, and pointy pumps in 2012. Eric Ryan/Getty Images The actress and producer arrived for the Louis Vuitton runway show in a lacy little white dress by the label and pointed-toe pumps. The black bra peeping through the lacy top of her dress feels as fashionable as it does international.

33 of 64 Rough Around the Edges Sarah Jessica Parker in a pink Oscar de la Renta gown with a black leather jacket in 2012. Gregory Pace/BEImages For the amfAR gala, Parker topped her pink Oscar de la Renta gown with a leather Theyskens' Theory jacket and added white gloves. The top of her outfit has a bit of edge to it, but the bottom works well to soften it up.

34 of 64 Rose on Her Shoulder Sarah Jessica Parker in a black blazer with jumbo pink flowers and white cropped pants in 2013. George Pimentel/WireImage For Target's Toronto opening, the style icon took a casual take on the menswear trend, opting for a classic black fitted blazer and white cropped pants. The pink and red floral accent on her left shoulder adds a bit of fun and color to this neutral 'fit.

35 of 64 Calling the Shots Sarah Jessica Parker in a black and gold stripe sequined Marc Jacobs dress in 2013. Daniel Deme/WENN.com At the Charlie and the Chocolate Factory press night at Theatre Royal in London, Parker lit up the red carpet in a black and gold stripe sequined Marc Jacobs dress that she paired with a Fendi baguette and black pointed-toe pumps.

36 of 64 Ballerina Inspired Sarah Jessica Parker in a white and blush pink Prabal Gurung top and white full skirt in 2013. Agostini/Invision/AP While attending the New York City Ballet Gala, the star wore a two-piece ensemble: a Prabal Gurung top and Olivier Theyskens full skirt. Between the white and pink color scheme and the dainty ribbon, it was very on theme for the ballet.

37 of 64 21st Century Flapper Sarah Jessica Parker in a silver Naeem Khan flapper-style fringe dress with black pumps in 2013. WENN.com Parker shimmered in a silver-gold beaded Naeem Khan fringe dress that was reminiscent of the flapper era—minus all the extra bells and whistles. She styled it with bangles, layered necklaces, and black pointed-toe pumps.

38 of 64 Modern Art Sarah Jessica Parker in a gold, paint-splattered Giles gown and a feathered headpiece in 2013. Dimitrios Kambouris/Getty Images At the Metropolitan Museum of Art's annual gala, the actress fully embodied the punk theme in a gold, paint-splattered Giles gown that she paired with a custom Philip Treacy mohawk headpiece.

39 of 64 Her Own Column Sarah Jessica Parker in a black, white, and fuchsia silk velvet column gown and sash in 2013. Dimitrios Kambouris/WireImage Parker paraded out a bold style statement at the amfAR New York Gala in this fuchsia silk velvet column gown and sash by Maison Martin Margiela. Her accesories were minimal, but the scarf is definitely standing on its own.

40 of 64 Show Your Stripes Sarah Jessica Parker in a multicolored striped skirt and top with purple pumps in 2014. Splash News Proving her street style status, SJP was snapped out in NYC in a red-and-white striped top that she expertly paired with a full-buttoned, chunky striped midi-length skirt.

41 of 64 Personalized Poncho Sarah Jessica Parker in a monogrammed Burberry blanket poncho and skinny jeans in 2014. Humberto Carreno/startraksphoto.com Parker was one of the first celebs to sport Burberry's hot-off-the-runway monogrammed blanket poncho. She paired the top with skinny jeans and burgundy wedges to help elongate her petite figure.

42 of 64 Silk on Silk on Silk Sarah Jessica Parker in a black Delphine Manivet dress with sheer panels in 2014. Splash News Always one to make a statement, SJP wowed in a triple silk organdi and velvet dress with tulle illusion panels from Delphine Manivet. Another head-turning look for the actress, which she wore to the Footwear News Achievement Awards and Hall of Fame Gala.

43 of 64 Belle of the Ball Sarah Jessica Parker wearing a black and white Oscar de la Renta dress with opera gloves in 2014. David Fisher/Rex/REX USA For the Costume Institute Gala Benefit celebrating the Charles James exhibit, the A-lister arrived dressed to the nines in an Oscar de la Renta gown and white gloves. The top of her dress has petal-like embellishments that sit perfectly on her hips.

44 of 64 Check'Er Out Sarah Jessica Parker in a black and white gingham coat and olive green bag 2015. Dara Kushner/INFphoto.com The Blue Night star upped her style game with a sleeveless coat in gingham, accessorizing her look with an olive bag and heels.

45 of 64 Corset Queen Sarah Jessica Parker wearing a black and white outfit with jewel-toned heels in 2016. Raymond Hall/Getty Images Who says black and white has to be boring? Certainly not Parker. Here, she made the colors pop by choosing a dress with layers of lace, sequins, and satin touches. And the corset helps keep the garments from losing structure.

46 of 64 Peek-a-Bra Sarah Jessica Parker in a sheer black dress with metallic purple boots in 2016. D Dipasupil/Getty Images Sarah Jessica Parker proved that shoes make the outfit by pairing a sheer black dress with head-turning purple boots. The hem of the dress hangs slightly over the top of the boot, which adds length to the 'fit.

47 of 64 Purple Reign Sarah Jessica Parker in a deep purple Dolce & Gabbana jewel dress and bronze pointed heels in 2016. Gilbert Carrasquillo/Getty Images The talented actress loves her lace. Here, she wowed in a Dolce & Gabbana dress covered in colorful gems. Her copper pumps added the perfect finishing touches to her look.

48 of 64 All About Fringe Sarah Jessica Parker in a navy, off-shoulder Monse fringe dress and black heels in 2017. James Devaney/Getty Images Go big or go home seems to be the motto for the Life Without Dick actress. Parker turned an evening at the New York City Ballet into a breathtaking fashion show with a twirl-worthy Monse dress.

49 of 64 Classy Intimates Sarah Jessica Parker in a black lace skirt, white lace top, and black Intimissimi bra in 2017. Gotham/Getty Images Parker somehow managed to make even an exposed bra look chic during Intimissimi's store opening in New York. What's even wilder is this wasn't the first time she pulled off the trend.

50 of 64 Carrie Fisher Tribute Sarah Jessica Parker in a white Vera Wang ballgown at the 2017 Golden Globes. Steve Granitz/Getty Images One of history's biggest fashion stars paid homage to Carrie Fisher with a twisted updo. But it was her Vera Wang dress that stole the show.

51 of 64 Playing With Textures Sarah Jessica Parker in a white lace top and teal satin skirt with white sandal heels in 2018. Daniele Venturelli/Getty Images The interplay of Parker's textured lace top with her smooth satin skirt is perfection. It's both sexy and tasteful, making it highly appropriate for the event: Intimissimi's Italian lingerie show.

52 of 64 Sky-High Slit Sarah Jessica Parker in a navy sequined dress with high slit in 2018. Pascal Le Segretain/Getty Images The bombshell wowed when she showed up to the premiere of Here and Now in this sultry navy number. With the all-over sparkle, flared sleeves, and high slit, she seemed to have invented a hot new style: disco glam.

53 of 64 Red Moment Sarah Jessica Parker in a voluminous red gown with sheer black arms and red heels in 2018. Gilbert Carrasquillo/WireImage At the New York City Ballet Fall Fashion Gala, the Divorce actress stepped out in this bright ballgown—with ruby slippers to match. While the dress's color and volume were enough to turn heads, the sheer black detailing on the sleeves and back was what made it next level.

54 of 64 A Whole Lot of Love Sarah Jessica Parker in a blue, teal, black, and gold dress with heart and hand patterns in 2019. Astrid Stawiarz/Getty Images At the 30th Annual GLAAD Media Awards, Parker was all smiles—and for stylistic reasons. Everything about her Elie Saab Fall 2019 gown, from its gorgeous fabric to its romantic puff sleeves, made her look like red carpet royalty.

55 of 64 For the People Sarah Jessica Parker in a bright pink overcoat, printed maxi dress, and Mary-Jane shoes in 2021. Jose Perez/Bauer-Griffin/GC Images Here, the shoe lover and entrepreneur was seen outside her eponymous store in NYC. Her footwear of choice? Classic Mary Janes.

56 of 64 Dusty Rose Sarah Jessica Parker in a two-toned gray and pink dress with cape in 2021. Dimitrios Kambouris/Getty Images SJP opted for a two-toned Oscar de la Renta dress complete with cape and tulle skirt for HBO Max's premiere of And Just Like That at the MoMA. It's her interpretation of balletcore.

57 of 64 Drippin' in Diamonds Sarah Jessica Parker in a pink dress with silver tulle, jewel-encrusted overlay in 2022. Roy Rochlin/Getty Images Parker looked like she came straight out of a fairy tale in this pink Prabal Gurung dress with silver tulle overlay. She was celebrating the opening night of the Neil Simon play Plaza Suite, in which she costars alongside husband, Matthew Broderick. The definition of a power couple.

58 of 64 Don't Be So Petticoat Sarah Jessica Parker in petticoat dress by Christopher John Rogers at the Met Gala in 2022. John Shearer/Getty Images The Met Gala is one of the most—if not the most—anticipated fashion events of the year. At the 2022 fête, Parker nailed the year's theme of In America: An Anthology of Fashion, by paying tribute to Elizabeth Hobbs Keckley, the first Black female fashion designer in the White House, with this petticoat dress by Christopher John Rogers.

59 of 64 Privé Island Sarah Jessica Parker in a floral coat with, pink cropped pants, and pink heels in 2022. Dimitrios Kambouris/Getty Images People were thrilled when Disney finally announced a sequel to one of the best Halloween films of all time. But even more thrilling? The gray, pink, and purple Armani Privé ensemble SJP wore to the Hocus Pocus 2 premiere.

60 of 64 Pearlescent Sarah Jessica Parker in a navy sequined dress, white overcoat, and tied pearl necklace in Dec. 2022. Bruce Glikas/WireImage Parker looked ravishing at the opening night of Some Like It Hot! on Broadway. Her sequined dress and pearl necklace, combined with the ivory overcoat, read as a modern take on light and dark pearls.

61 of 64 Black Swan Sarah Jessica Parker at the New York City Ballet Fall Fashion Gala in October 2023. Cindy Ord/Getty Images Sarah Jessica Parker is no stranger to looking cute or drop-dead gorgeous. This off-shoulder dress with small keyhole accents and a puffy tulle skirt is a quintessential look for the Did You Hear About the Morgans? star. And the mismatched heels bring that wink that's classic in SJP's looks.

62 of 64 "Garden of Time" Gown Sarah Jessica Parker attends the 2024 Met Gala in Richard Quinn. Jeff Kravitz/FilmMagic Talk about an eye-catching outfit. From the extravagant headpiece covering SJP's face to the jewel-encrusted, structured ball gown, this "Garden of Time" ensemble by British designer Richard Quinn invites fans to look a bit closer at its ephemeral details.

63 of 64 All the Metals Sarah Jessica Parker at the Red Sea International Film Festival in Saudi Arabia in December 2024. Ernesto S. Ruscio/Getty Images for The Red Sea International Film Festival Parker's dress for the Red Sea International Film Festival in Saudi Arabia used silver (on top), gold (in the middle), and bronze (at the bottom) to give a metallic vibe. The dress has tons of sparkle and movement, thanks to the fringe on the skirt.
